##### PARTICLE SPECTRA                                            2037 1451
                                                                  2037 1451
For Ca-44, an adjustment of the default matrix element            2037 1451
parameterization of [kon04b] for pre-equilibrium reactions of a   2037 1451
factor of 0.7 was needed, to describe the aforementioned cross    2037 1451
sections and emission spectra for nuclides in this mass range.    2037 1451
For high-energy neutron and charged particle spectra, the average 2037 1451
quality is also determined by the pre-equilibrium model and its   2037 1451
global parameterization. No high-energy experiments are           2037 1451
available, though neutron induced reaction spectra between 28 and 2037 1451
63 MeV on Al [ben02], Si [ben02b] and Fe [sly03] have enabled us  2037 1451
to better constrain the results, through the aforementioned       2037 1451
matrix element, for particle yields and double-differential       2037 1451
spectra for all ejectiles up to alpha particles.                  2037 1451
